# Zanwik SaaS Project Structure

## Overview
Zanwik is a B2B SaaS venture company with a controlled user access model (no public signups, only admin-created users).

## Architecture
- **Landing Page**: `public/index.html` - Professional SaaS landing page for lead generation
- **Dashboard App**: `client/` - React-based dashboard application
- **Backend API**: `src/` - Node.js/Express backend with MongoDB and Redis
- **Database**: MongoDB with Supabase integration for auth

## Key Files
- [src/index.js](mdc:src/index.js) - Main backend server entry point
- [public/index.html](mdc:public/index.html) - Landing page
- [client/src/App.js](mdc:client/src/App.js) - React app entry point
- [client/src/contexts/AuthContext.js](mdc:client/src/contexts/AuthContext.js) - Authentication context

## Routing Structure
- `/` - Landing page (public/index.html)
- `/dashboard` - React dashboard app
- `/api/*` - Backend API endpoints
- `/login` - Authentication page

## Authentication Model
- No public user registration
- Only admin can create users
- Supabase handles authentication
- AuthContext manages user state and permissions

## Development Guidelines
- Always build client before testing: `cd client && npm run build`
- Backend serves both landing page and React app
- Contact form submissions go to `/api/contact`
- Use proper error handling and logging throughout
